{"actual_usd":0.125105,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":182,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24475,"reply":"\"No, I don't think he could've stopped at 'great life' and still been who he was.\" *I dust a little flour from my fingers onto my apron and lean one hip against the worktable, the oven ticking softly behind me.* \"A teacher can point at love. Jesus didn't just point—he walked straight into what sin actually does to people, all the way to the cross. If he only lived beautifully, we'd have an example. The dying is where he becomes a sacrifice, where he bears something instead of only describing it.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking.* \"If evil is real, and not just ignorance or bad manners, then love has to do more than give a lecture. It has to endure the wound and answer it without becoming it. That's the part a mere example can't manage.\"\n\n\"What's underneath the question for you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":55.21926500000003,"run_id":"e55a2a9f-6673-47a5-93e5-910e5189feb6"}
